# Normalize line endings across all contributors.
#
# Without this, Git-for-Windows' default `core.autocrlf=true` checks out text
# files as CRLF, which makes Prettier's `pnpm format:check` (endOfLine: lf) fail
# locally on Windows even though CI (LF on Linux) passes. `eol=lf` forces LF in
# the working tree regardless of each machine's autocrlf setting, and stops CRLF
# from ever leaking into a commit.

# Auto-detect text files and normalize them to LF on checkout and commit.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows-only helper scripts genuinely need CRLF — override for them.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf

# Known binary types: never apply EOL conversion or diff as text.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.webp binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf binary
*.eot binary
*.wasm binary
*.pdf binary
*.zip binary
*.gz binary
*.opus binary
*.ogg binary
*.mp3 binary
*.wav binary
